│ The patch still fails because the transformation introduces undefined behavior (UB) even after freezing the `poison` value. The issue lies in the fact that the scalarization process does not fully preserve the │
│ semantics of the vector operation. Specifically, the vector operation allows for `poison` elements, while the scalar operation does not.                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ To resolve this, we need to ensure that the transformation does not proceed if the scalarization would introduce UB. This means we should avoid scalarizing the `sdiv` operation entirely if the divisor is       │
│ `poison`. I will revise the patch to include this fix.                                                                                                                                                            │
